  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\n#1816 indicates that we're experiencing some congestion when transmitting _many_ transactions concurrently.\r\n\r\nthis is likely due to how tx are broadcasted and waited for\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/0342bc24b7d248d3049ca7cf78caf6df59a81e52/cli/src/cmd/forge/script/receipts.rs#L53\r\n\r\ninstead of join_all, let's do a buffered stream here https://docs.rs/futures/latest/futures/stream/trait.StreamExt.html#method.buffered\r\n\r\nsomething like ` futures::stream::iter(tasks).buffered(<some reasonable limit>)`, perhaps 10-20 is reasonable.\r\n\r\n\r\neven better would be to make this a to step process that first sends all, then waits for receipts, ideally, we can turn this whole process in a custom Stream type, but let's do the `buffered` stream fix first\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
